{
  "id": 5156290162720768,
  "name": "RTCDegradationPreference enum value \"maintain-framerate-and-resolution\"",
  "summary": "\"maintain-framerate-and-resolution\" disables WebRTC's internal video adaptation. This enables the application to implement its own adaptation logic and prevents interference from the internal adaptation.\r\n\r\nFrom https://www.w3.org/TR/mst-content-hint/#dom-rtcdegradationpreference-maintain-framerate-and-resolution:\r\n\r\nMaintain framerate and resolution regardless of video quality. The user agent SHOULD NOT prefer reducing the framerate or resolution for quality and performance reasons, but MAY drop frames before encoding if necessary not to overuse network and encoder resources.",
  "markdown_fields": [],
  "blink_components": [
    "Blink>WebRTC>PeerConnection"
  ],
