  "motivation": "WebRTC has an internal video adaptation mechanism that optimizes video quality and performance by adjusting encoding settings. This mechanism relies on hardcoded logic and thresholds, which may not yield optimal results across diverse use cases. Application may benefit from implementing and using its own, external adaptation. For the external adaptation to work properly, the internal one needs to be disabled. \"maintain-framerate-and-resolution\" allows to disable the WebRTC's internal adaptation.\n\nWebRTC WG presentation: https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/11rr8X4aOao1AmvyoDLX8o9CPCmnDHkWGRM3nB4Q_104/edit?slide=id.g3657813d9b5_0_0#slide=id.g3657813d9b5_0_0",
